fr.cnrs.iees.graph

Interface GraphElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Identifiable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataEdge, DataNode, Edge, Node, ReadOnlyDataEdge, ReadOnlyDataNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataEdgeImpl, DataNodeImpl, EdgeAdapter, GraphElementAdapter, NodeAdapter, ReadOnlyDataEdgeImpl, ReadOnlyDataNodeImpl, SimpleEdgeImpl, SimpleNodeImpl

    public interface GraphElement
extends fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable, Identifiable
    The base features common to Edges and Nodes of a graph. NB: all elements must be cloneable
    Author:
    gignoux - 17 ao√ªt 2017 DECISION: as of 30/8/2017 I decided to get rid of the fluent API interface - it's messing too much with the OOP hierarchy and generates too many 'just typecasting' descendant methods. TODO: remove all the fluency I added before

      • traversal

        java.util.Collection<Node> traversal(int distance)
        As traversal(), but stopping after distance recursion steps. For example, node.traversal(1) will return only node, while node.traversal(2) will return all the Nodes connected with only 1 edge to this one.
        Parameters:
        distance - the number of recursion steps to search
        Returns:
        the connected Graph containing this instance
